<paragraph blockId="9.[264,970,1224,1285]" box="[264,422,1259,1285]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
(
<figureCitation box="[273,413,1259,1285]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–16" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1096,1120]" captionTargetBox="[385,1204,653,1062]" captionTargetId="figure-350@10.[375,1212,649,1070]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 14–16. Chrysotimus chikuni sp. nov. (male). 14. First flagellomere, lateral view; 15. genitalia, lateral view, 16. tip of genitalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048648/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs. 14–16</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1322,1339,1885]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Diagnosis. Four dc, acr absent. Hind tarsomere 1 with about 22 erect short black ventral bristles on basal 1/4 and row of 8–9 pv. Epandrium apically with finger­like lateral process</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1322,1339,1885]" box="[312,1187,1419,1445]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[463,533,1419,1445]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Male.</emphasis>
Body length 
<quantity box="[692,865,1419,1445]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="2.55" metricValueMin="2.35" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="2.45" valueMax="2.55" valueMin="2.35">2.35–2.55 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[1024,1183,1419,1445]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4749999999999996" metricValueMax="2.55" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="2.4749999999999996" valueMax="2.55" valueMin="2.4">2.4–2.55 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1322,1339,1885]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Head metallic green with pale gray pollen; frons and face brilliant. Hairs and bristles on head yellow. Ocellar tubercle weak, with 2 very long oc and 2 very short posterior hairs. Lower postocular bristles (including ventral hairs) pale. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[1112,1198,1539,1565]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–16" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1096,1120]" captionTargetBox="[385,1204,653,1062]" captionTargetId="figure-350@10.[375,1212,649,1070]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 14–16. Chrysotimus chikuni sp. nov. (male). 14. First flagellomere, lateral view; 15. genitalia, lateral view, 16. tip of genitalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048648/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
) blackish; first flagellomere blackish, rather short, about 0.7 times as long as wide; arista subdorsal, with basal segment very short. Proboscis blackish, with brown hairs; palpus brown, with yellow hairs and 2 yellow apical bristles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1322,1339,1885]" lastBlockId="10.[264,1322,284,550]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Thorax metallic green with pale gray pollen, mesonotum and scutellum brilliant. Hairs and bristles on thorax yellow; 4 strong dc, acr absent; scutellum with 2 pairs of bristles. Propleuron with 1 yellowish hair on lower portion. Legs including coxae yellow, with all tarsomere 5 brown. Hairs and bristles on legs yellow; coxae with yellow hairs and bristles; fore coxa with 5–6 anterior and apical bristles, mid coxa with 4–6 anterior and apical bris­ tles, hind coxa with 1 yellow outer bristle near middle. Fore femur with 1 short av and short 1 pv apically; mid femur with 1 av apically; hind femur with 1 av and 1 pv apically. Mid tibia with 2 ad and 2 pd, apically with 4 bristles; hind tibia with 2 ad and 2 pd, apically with 4 bristles. Fore tarsomere 1 with row of about 10 short v; hind tarsomere 1 with group of about 22 erect short black ventral bristles on basal 1/4 and row of 8–9 pv. Relative lengths of tibia and 5 tarsomeres of legs. LI 2.9: 2.2: 0.9: 0.7: 0.5: 0.4; LII 4.8: 2.5: 0.9: 0.8: 0.4: 0.4; LIII 5.5: 2.0: 1.0: 0.8: 0.5: 0.5.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048648" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5048648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048648/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" startId="10.[264,382,1096,1120]" targetBox="[385,1204,653,1062]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1322,1096,1155]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,466,1096,1120]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">FIGURES 14–16.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Wang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert, 2005" authorityName="Wang &amp; Yang &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2005" box="[476,699,1097,1120]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chikuni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[476,699,1097,1120]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Chrysotimus chikuni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[709,795,1097,1120]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(male). 14. First flagellomere, lateral view; 15. genitalia, lateral view, 16. tip of genitalia, ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1323,1246,1875]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Wing hyaline, veins brownish; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[699,729,1259,1276]" fontSize="7" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">4+5</subScript>
and M parallel apically, CuAx ratio 0.21. Squama yellow with pale yellow hairs. Halter brownish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1323,1246,1875]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Abdomen metallic green with pale gray pollen, dorsum brilliant. Hairs and bristles on abdomen yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1323,1246,1875]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[495,638,1409,1435]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–16" captionStartId="10.[264,382,1096,1120]" captionTargetBox="[385,1204,653,1062]" captionTargetId="figure-350@10.[375,1212,649,1070]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 14–16. Chrysotimus chikuni sp. nov. (male). 14. First flagellomere, lateral view; 15. genitalia, lateral view, 16. tip of genitalia, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5048648" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5048648/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Figs. 15–16</figureCitation>
). Epandrium distinctly longer than wide, apically with finger­like lateral process; surstylus rather thick and rounded apically, curved at middle; cercus with broad base and acute apex, with moderately long hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[264,1323,1246,1875]" box="[312,536,1529,1555]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
